name: Greed Force - 7 Inches Of Disappointment 7"
description:
Debut EP from Anarcho-D-Beat wasters Greed Force from SE, UK.
Co-released by Suburban White Trash Rec., Anarchotic Rec., Rantipole Zine & A World We Never Made.

"If Crass weren't hippies this would be what they'd sound like" - Suburban White Trash Records

Pressing info: 250 Black Wax, 125 Red Wax, 125 White Wax

All copies include a insert with lyrics and a download code that includes the samples the pressing plant wouldn't allow...

name: Blatoidea - Infected CD Album
description:
Debut, full-length album from Italian, London based cockroach punx Blatoidea. Out Now and available to purchase online from here, from the band at shows and from All Ages Records in Camden, London. 

Co-released by A World We Never Made, Death Or Glory, Bomb-All Records, Nuclear Chaos and No Label Records.

Comes with lyrics booklet housed in a cellophane-wrapped Digipack.

name: Ratbite (USA) / Ratbite (UKR) Split CD
description:
Split CD featuring two bands both called Ratbite, one from the United States and one from Ukraine.

Co-released by A World We Never Made (UK) & Suburban White Trash Records (US). 

Limited to 300 copies.

name: Cleavers / Clowns Split 7"
description:
Labels: Da Da Tunes (Scotland), A World We Never Made (England), Our New Planet Records (Australia)
Format: Vinyl, 7", 45 RPM
Released: 13 Apr 2012

Tracklist▼
Cleavers Side
A1 Girls In Their Sunday Best
A2 Hulk Hands	
A3 A Casual Box
Clowns Side
B1 Eat A Gun	
B2 You Want It, You Got It
B3 Fight Me

Limited to 250 copies. 
Split release featuring Elgin's Cleavers and Melbourne's Clowns. 
Released on labels from Scotland, England and Australia.

Comes with three, one-sided 10x12 cards for Cleavers, Clowns & Wolf Mask, which include info and download links. 
Some copies come with a free patch while stokes last.
